# Plugin YAML Schema

- plugin properties are described in YAML and validated using JSON schema
- using the 'buildkite-plugin-linter' you can ensure your `plugin.yml` file is compliant with the Buildkite plugin schema 

## Plugin.yml configuration object

- when writing a plugin the `configuration` object in the `plugin.yml` file is used to define the properties that can be passed to your plugin from your pipeline
- [JSON schema](https://json-schema.org/) is used to validate the YAML

- the properties object of your `plugin.yml` file can contain something something any types as many items as you need

